# Domain Model

Full specification: `Requirements.md`. Key facts for feature work.

## Entity Hierarchy
```
User
└── Organization (personal org auto-created; user can belong to many)
    └── Exam (archived, not deleted)
        └── Version (exactly one active at a time; activating auto-deactivates previous)
            └── Section (draws N questions from its pool per attempt)
                └── Question (pool member; min 1 phrasing; can move between sections)
                    └── Answer / Blank / Item / Pair
```

## Roles (per Organization)
| Role | Key permissions |
|------|----------------|
| Owner | Full control, manage members, delete org, bulk-delete results |
| Editor | Create/edit exams, manage restricted-exam allowlists |
| Grader | Grade manual questions, view analytics |
| Viewer | Read-only: results, analytics, exam details |

## Question Types
| Type | Grading |
|------|---------|
| Multiple choice | Auto (% weights); optional negative scoring for wrong picks |
| Open-ended | Manual; configurable char limit (default 255) |
| Fill-in-the-blank | Per-blank: exact match, Python regex, or manual; `{{n}}` syntax |
| Drag-and-drop ordering | Auto: all-or-nothing or partial `(correct/total × pts)` |
| Matching | Auto: all-or-nothing or partial `(correct pairs/left items × pts)`; one-to-one |
| Informational | Unscored |

## Key Business Rules
- Usernames are globally unique but changeable; internal IDs never change
- Personal org slug = username slug — changes when username changes (warn users)
- Section "questions to draw" must be 1 ≤ N ≤ pool size; unset = use all
- Attempt history shows names snapshotted at submission time
- Percentage approval threshold = `pct × max_possible_score` for that attempt
- Grading queue locks an attempt while a grader is working; lock expires on idle timeout
- All UI strings must use i18n keys — no hardcoded copy
